## The Keyword Trap: Why "ATS Friendly" Isn't Enough

Traditional ATS platforms are essentially basic search engines built on 2010-era logic. They rely on "string matching." If a recruiter searches for a "React Developer" and your resume lists you as a "Frontend Engineer with deep expertise in Next.js and Vue," a legacy system might rank you lower simply because the exact character string "React Developer" didn't appear enough times.

This "keyword soup" madness forces high-level developers to write for robots instead of humans. It strips away the context of your achievements and replaces it with a checklist. At **GetHired**, we believe that the **technical resume review** process is fundamentally broken.

